{
  "_README": "Full-scale / ring corroded-pipe BURST tests: measured failure pressure vs B31G prediction. Validates the metal-loss engine (b31g.js failurePressure) against real bursts -- the engine's predicted P_f (SF=1) is compared to the measured burst pressure. yield_MPa is the ACTUAL measured yield of each specimen (used as SMYS so the comparison isolates method error, not material over-strength). Defect = single axial metal-loss patch / cluster envelope (length L, max depth d). All values transcribed from the cited source tables; nothing fabricated or read off a figure. Run via ../benchmark/run.js. All 18 IDTS values are double-verified: Benjamin 2016 (IJPVP 145) Table 8 (PRIMARY) and Mousavi 2020 (EFA 108:104284) Table 4 (secondary) agree exactly with the stored numbers. Verified against the Benjamin PRIMARY full text (Table 6 geometry + Table 8 burst); the database contains exactly these 18 specimens (no more), and b31g.js reproduces the paper's own published B31G predictions (Table 9: IDTS 13 -> 22.24 vs 22.2, IDTS 14 -> 22.87 vs 22.9 MPa) -- pinned in test-b31g.js. | [2026-06-01 EXPANSION] +33 specimens: 32 full-scale bursts of pipe sections from operating pipelines with single isolated REAL corrosion defects (Cronin 2000, Waterloo PhD, UWSpace open access), spanning API 5L X42/X46/X52/X56 and OD 273-864 mm, each geometry-verified against Cronin's own tabulated B31G prediction (systematic -2..-6% variant offset, same sign across all rows = extraction confirmed); + 1 X65 hydrostatic burst (He & Zhao 2024, MDPI JMSE, Test 1). Total specimens now 52 (was 19). The original 18 Benjamin MTI-JIP IDTS + 1 Qi note above still refers to that machined-defect subset.",
  "sources": {
    "BENJAMIN2016": "Benjamin A.C., Freire J.L.F., Vieira R.D., Cunha D.J.S., Interaction of corrosion defects in pipelines - Part 2: MTI JIP database of corroded pipe tests, Int. J. Press. Vessels Pip. 145 (2016) 41-59, DOI 10.1016/j.ijpvp.2016.06.006. PRIMARY source of the IDTS 13-30 series: full-scale hydrotest-to-failure of API 5L X70 (OD 457.2 mm, t ~7.9 mm) with spark-eroded defect colonies. Measured failure pressures = Table 8; cluster geometry = Table 6; per-tube yields = Table 1.",
    "EFA2020": "Mousavi S.S., Moghaddam A.S., Failure pressure estimation error for corroded pipeline using various revisions of ASME B31G, Engineering Failure Analysis 108 (2020) 104284, DOI 10.1016/j.engfailanal.2019.104284. Secondary tabulation of the same IDTS series (its Table 4); used to cross-verify every value.",
    "QI2023": "Qi C. et al., Experiments and evaluation on residual strength of X52 steel pipe with various internal defects, Front. Energy Res. 10 (2023) 1046900, DOI 10.3389/fenrg.2022.1046900",
    "CRONIN2000": "Cronin D.S., \"Assessment of Corrosion Defects in Pipelines\", PhD thesis, Dept. of Mechanical Engineering, University of Waterloo, 2000 (UWSpace, open access: uwspace.uwaterloo.ca). Full-scale burst tests of pipe sections removed from operating pipelines, each containing a single isolated REAL corrosion defect. Geometry (OD, wall thickness, SMYS/actual YS/UTS), measured failure pressure, max defect depth and defect length from Table 4.2.1; per-model predictions (original B31G, RSTRENG, PCORRC, Ritchie&Last) from the page-182 table. Tables extracted with PyMuPDF find_tables(); every stored specimen's geometry was independently VERIFIED by reproducing Cronin's own tabulated original-B31G prediction with b31g.js to within a systematic -2..-6% (a B31G-variant offset that is the same sign across ALL specimens, confirming correct column extraction). 8 of 40 rows were excluded because their defect depth/length did not extract cleanly.",
    "HEZHAO2024": "He P., Zhao B., \"Experimental and Numerical Analysis of the Impact of Corrosion on the Failure Pressure of API 5L X65 Pipeline\", J. Mar. Sci. Eng. 12(10):1810, 2024, DOI 10.3390/jmse12101810 (MDPI, open access). Test Pipeline 1 hydrostatic burst: OD 325 mm, t 12 mm (Table 3), defect length 395 mm (l/D 1.215) and max depth 9.3 mm (d/t 0.775) (Table 5), measured failure pressure 11.4 MPa (Sec. 3.4, text). API 5L X65, actual yield 545 MPa (Table 2). Tests 2-4 reported only as normalized pf/p0 and were excluded (no directly-tabulated absolute burst pressure)."
  },
